The residents of Mammy Market settlement at 3 Battalion, Nigeria Army, Effurun Barracks, Delta State, were full of joy as the Rotary Club of Effurun donated 3 manual pump boreholes to them to improve water supply to the area. Speaking while donating the boreholes to the residents of Mammy Market, the president of Rotary Club of Effurun, District 9141, Rotarian Michael Enehizena said the club constructed the three boreholes to assist the people of the area. Rotarian Enehizena said that Rotary in the month of March celebrates the month of water, sanitation and hygiene and that they decided to use this period to make the donation of the water projects to help facilitate settlement access to good water. He noted that Club members use many avenues for humanitarian services, adding that there are programmes to address such concerns as health care, hunger, poverty, sanitation, illiteracy and environment as a way of assisting the society. Rotarian Enehizena said that with the commissioning of these water boreholes the residents of Mammy Market have become the owners of the boreholes and should maintain it to their benefit.